Ukraine Seeks to Remove Restrictions on Sale of State Assets

-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 
2011-06-25T14:45:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-25/ukraine-seeks-to-remove-restrictions-on-sale-of-state-assets.html
Ukraine is seeking to remove
restrictions on the sale of state assets.  Prime Minister  Mykola Azarov ’s government wants to allow
the sale of aviation companies, producers of railway machinery
and ports to improve management, according to a draft bill
submitted to parliament and published on the legislature’s
 website  today.  The nation also want to allow the sale of parts of state-
owned company Khlib Ukrainy, according to the draft.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
